Ya kamata Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take bayarwa don bunkasa ilimin kere kere
Kamar yadda kasar Sin ke kara shiga harkar kere kere, Amurka ta kamata ta ninka kudaden da take kashewa wajen bincike a wannan fannin, a cewar Kai Fu Lee, mai zuba jari da kuma mai sana'ar kere kere, wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple.
Kalamansa sun zo ne bayan da wasu bangarori na gwamnatin Amurka suka kawo sanarwar game da ilimin artificial intelligence, duk da cewa Amurka ba ta da tsarin dabarun fasaha.
Kasar Sin, a nata bangaren, ta gabatar da wani shiri a bara kuma tana da burin zama ta farko a fannin kirkirar kere kere na fasaha nan da shekarar 2030.
"Abu ne mai kyau a fara da ninka kasafin kudin bincike kan ilimin kere kere, domin duk sauran kasashe suna baya da Amurka, kuma muna neman babbar nasara ta gaba", in ji Lee.
"Tallafin tattalin arziki na iya ninka damar da babbar nasara ta gaba a fannin kere kere za ta fito daga Amurka", in ji Lee a wata hira da CNBC a wannan makon.
Lee, wanda littafinsa AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order aka buga ta Houghton Mifflin Harcourt a wannan watan, shi ne daraktan Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin kere kere na kasar Sin, Face++.
A cikin shekarun 1980, ya yi aiki a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon don haɓaka tsarin hankali na wucin gadi wanda ya doke mafi kyawun wasan Othello na Amurka, kuma daga baya ya kasance jagora a Microsoft Research ko darektan sashen China na Google.
Lee ya amince da gasar fasahar zamani ta gwamnatin Amurka, kamar ta Robotics Challenge ta hukumar bincike ta Defense Advanced Research Projects, kuma ya tambayi lokacin da za a gudanar da na gaba, domin taimakawa wajen gano masu basira na gaba.
Masu bincike a Amurka sukan yi aiki tukuru domin samun tallafin gwamnati, a cewar Lee.
"Ba kasar Sin ce ke satar shugabannin jami'o'i ba, kamfanoni ne", in ji Lee.
Facebook, Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun yi amfani da manyan mutane daga jami'o'i don yin aiki a kan ilimin kere kere a shekarun baya bayan nan.
Lee ya ce sauye-sauye a cikin manufofin shige da fice na iya taimaka wa Amurka wajen karfafa kokarinta a fannin ilimin kere kere.
"Ina ganin cewa ya kamata masu samun digirin digirin digirgir a fannin ilimin kere kere su samu takardar izinin zama ta atomatik", in ji shi.
Majalisar dokokin kasar Sin ta fitar da shirin bunkasa fasahar kere kere na Next Generation Artificial Intelligence a watan Yulin 2017.
Kamfanin Kimiyya na Kasa na kasar Sin na tallafa wa ma'aikatan jami'o'i,kamar yadda National Science Foundation da sauran hukumomin gwamnati ke ba da kudade ga masu bincike a Amurka,amma ingancin aikin kimiyya ya fi na kasar Sin, a cewar Lee.
A farkon wannan shekarar ma, Ma'aikatar Tsaro ta Amurka ta kafa wani cibiyar bincike mai amfani da fasaha ta Joint Artificial Intelligence Center, wanda zai hada da masana'antu da masana kimiyya, kuma fadar White House ta sanar da kafa wani kwamitin bincike mai amfani da fasaha.
Kuma a wannan watan, DARPA ta sanar da zuba jari na dala biliyan biyu a wani shiri da ake kira AI Next.
Game da NSF, a yanzu haka suna zuba jari fiye da dala miliyan 100 a binciken ilimin kere kere.
