Cutar HIV/AIDS: China ta ruwaito karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sabbin kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta ruwaito cewa yawan mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da kuma cutar kanjamau ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Fiye da mutane 820 000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar, in ji wakilin lafiya.
Kusan sabbin cututtuka 40 000 ne aka ruwaito a cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kawai.
Mafi yawan sababbin cututtuka ana watsa su ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda hakan ya nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar hiv ta yadu cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin ta hanyar kamuwa da jini.
Amma adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya kusan kusan sifili, in ji wani jami'in kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma duk da haka, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a China ya ƙaru da mutum 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i na zama babbar matsala a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An yi wa luwadi laifi a kasar Sin a 1997, amma ana ganin cewa ana nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT.
Saboda dabi'un da suka fi na masu ra'ayin mazan jiya, wasu bincike sun nuna cewa kashi 70-90 cikin dari na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata.
Yawancin cututtuka suna faruwa ne saboda rashin isasshen kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan yanayi.
Tun 2003, hukumomin kasar Sin sun yi alkawarin samun maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a matsayin wani mataki na magance matsalar.
